Vice President Joe Biden wrote an op-ed in The Wall Street Journal discussing the economic and political progress in the Americas. He highlighted his visit to Colombia and the positive impact of the U.S. free-trade agreement with the country. Biden also mentioned the growing middle class in Latin America and the region's potential for economic partnership with the U.S. He emphasized the Obama administration's commitment to engagement with the Americas, including recent trips to Mexico and Costa Rica. Biden noted the importance of economic integration and openness, as well as the Alliance of the Pacific, a trade pact among Chile, Colombia, Peru, and Mexico. He discussed the significance of energy partnership with Brazil and the need for democratic protections and citizen security. Biden acknowledged the challenges in the region, such as drug policy and immigration, but stressed the importance of respectful and honest discussions. He concluded by envisioning a solidly middle-class, secure, and democratic Americas.